Colombian Stock Movers: Cementos Argos, Ecopetrol Advance

-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 
2011-10-04T17:19:38Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-04/colombian-stock-movers-cementos-argos-ecopetrol-advance.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 12:46 p.m. New York time.  The IGBC Index fell 0.4 percent to 12,466.57 while the
Colcap Index was little changed at 1,551.25.  Cementos Argos SA (CEMARGOS)  ,  Colombia ’s biggest cement
maker, rose 0.2 percent to 10,580 pesos. The company said it
completed its $760 million purchase of U.S. assets of Lafarge
SA, the world’s biggest cement producer, according to a
regulatory filing.  Ecopetrol SA (ECOPETL)  , Colombia’s largest oil company,
rose 0.9 percent to 3,790 pesos. The company said it found oil
in the Trasgo-1 well in the Cano Sur block with average
production of 120 barrels per day, according to a regulatory
filing yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blake Schmidt in Bogota at 
 bschmidt16@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
